<br>
Did you ever notice the ability to cause aggro is completly opposite if who can take the hits ?<br>
<br>
Warr<br>
SK/Pal<br>
Clr/Bard/ranger<br>
Rogue/monk/shamy<br>
Ench/Wiz/Nec/Mage<br>
<br>
As far as i am concered any caster class can out aggro every other class . If you don't belive me go tell a wizard to pull for a group and see what happens<br>
<br>
If you really think about it this entire game is based around aggro , who has aggro and how much . You just have to give it to the right people while maintaining a succficient amount of damage . <br>
<br>
The problem is that when you reach the top of the classes , the first one has barley any aggro , but can take the hits . The next one down creates thier own and have a sufficent amount a HP so it's still possible to tank. Thus the problem . <br>
<br>
I think the best solution for this , if one needs to be implmented is give a new taunt formula . Let's say for warriors it caps at 500 hate for them , but only 250 on other class and based soley on RNG , that gives warrior more chance to taunt better , but still maintaining a decent chance they will have very little aggro .<br>
<br>
I mean let's face it , if you give them too much more aggro with thier now 2 augmented hate generating weapons , the game would be trivial . If the best tank always got aggro quickly the only thing that is going to stop the force is if the clerics go oom .<br>
